However  another important rerating driver could emerge if the group successfully exits its held-to-maturity (HTM) investments. HTM assets account for 51% of its equity value and is an overhang for its share price due to it‚Äôs a lack of transparency. In addition  it has no synergy with its shipbuilding segment.
